sentences: Andrew Charles Cyrille (born November 10, 1939) is an American avant-garde jazz drummer.
He joined the Cecil Taylor unit in 1965, and worke with Taylor over a period of 15 years.
He later formed a musical partnership with Milford Graves, and the two recorded a drum duet album in 1974.

He began studying science at St. John's University, but was already playing jazz in the evenings and switched his studies to the Juilliard School.
He joined the Cecil Taylor unit in 1965, and worke with Taylor over a period of 15 years.
Cyrille is currently a member of the group, Trio 3, with Oliver Lake and Reggie Workman.
Spring of Two Blue J's (Unit Core, 1973)
